<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1931-02-24T17:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1931-02-24T17:00:00-05:00" n="721" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d721">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">711.632/94a: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Minister in Austria</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Stockton</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1931-02-24T17:00:00-05:00">February 24, 1931—5
                                p.m.</date></dateline></opener>
                        <p>9. Advice and consent of Senate to ratification of supplementary
                            agreement given February 20. Instrument of ratification of treaty and
                            supplementary agreement will be forwarded for exchange at Vienna upon
                            advice by you by cable that Austria is prepared to effect exchange.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Stimson</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>